Sky emission¶

load_sky_emission[source]

load_sky_emission(config_sky_emission, site, channel)

Load foreground maps for a channel

Parameters¶

config_sky_emission : dict CMB-S4 sky emission configuration, generally config['sky_emission'] for a configuration loaded from a TOML file dictionary with standard emission names and their weights site : str 'Pole' or 'Chile', case doesn't matter channel : str Channel tag, e.g. 'MFHS1'

Returns¶

output_map : numpy array Output map with all emissions combined, uses nan for missing pixels

## inputs

ch = "LFS1"
site = "Chile"

output_map = load_sky_emission(config["sky_emission"], site, ch)
